Maternal mortality, fetal death, congenital anomalies and infant mortality at an advanced maternal age. Recent economic, technological, and social changes in Hungary have altered the role of women and thus patterns of childbearing.  In 1986, 65.9% of births in Hungary involved mothers in the 20-29-year age group--generally regarded as the optimal period for childbearing.  The distribution of the remaining births by age group was as follows:  19 years or under, 13.6% 30-34 years, 15.3%